1
00:00:09,458 --> 00:00:10,958
[gunfire]

2
00:00:15,625 --> 00:00:17,583
The antiquated history
you worship

3
00:00:17,666 --> 00:00:19,375
will be rewritten by my hand!

4
00:00:21,791 --> 00:00:22,708
[roars]

5
00:00:22,791 --> 00:00:24,208
[yells]

6
00:00:28,125 --> 00:00:30,583
♪

7
00:00:33,541 --> 00:00:36,416
It’s time for the curtain
to be raised at last!

8
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:43,666
No. It’s impossible.

9
00:00:43,750 --> 00:00:46,083
No one has ever broken
through the Heavenly Gate.

10
00:00:46,166 --> 00:00:47,833
Sir! What are your orders?

11
00:00:47,916 --> 00:00:49,375
We need to halt
the enemy’s incursion

12
00:00:49,458 --> 00:00:51,000
before they reach
the palace.

13
00:00:51,083 --> 00:00:52,250
I-- Right!

14
00:00:52,333 --> 00:00:54,583
Drive back this
rebel scum, men!

15
00:00:54,666 --> 00:00:56,958
No. Kill every last one of them!

16
00:00:57,041 --> 00:00:58,416
[GARRISON LEADER]
Yes, sir!

17
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:00,708
You won’t
survive the night, Liscar!

18
00:01:00,791 --> 00:01:03,250
♪

19
00:01:10,833 --> 00:01:14,291
Are you trying to follow
in my footsteps, Diese?

20
00:01:14,375 --> 00:01:16,083
A foolish endeavor.

21
00:01:17,333 --> 00:01:19,375
Pardon, where
are you going, sir?

22
00:01:20,375 --> 00:01:22,791
Into the battle to deal
with this myself.

23
00:01:22,875 --> 00:01:25,041
I’ve never been much
for waiting on others.

24
00:01:28,666 --> 00:01:29,875
[MARLYA gasps]

25
00:01:29,958 --> 00:01:32,500
They managed to breach
the Heavenly Gate!

26
00:01:32,583 --> 00:01:34,250
-What now, sir?
-[FREE growls]

27
00:01:34,333 --> 00:01:37,375
We stop Beevee Liscar.
Let’s move out!

28
00:01:37,458 --> 00:01:38,458
[FREE grunts]

29
00:03:13,708 --> 00:03:16,708
[gunfire]

30
00:03:18,625 --> 00:03:21,166
[metal scraping]

31
00:03:23,958 --> 00:03:25,625
-[SOLDIERS gasping]
-What have we here?

32
00:03:25,708 --> 00:03:27,125
A pile of rubble!

33
00:03:27,208 --> 00:03:28,458
[SOLDIERS groaning]

34
00:03:33,750 --> 00:03:35,458
You’re dust!
Meant to scatter!

35
00:03:38,875 --> 00:03:39,791
[SOLDIERS inhales sharply]

36
00:03:47,250 --> 00:03:48,583
-[squelching]
-[heavy thud]

37
00:03:54,916 --> 00:03:56,208
You lacked resolve.

38
00:03:56,291 --> 00:03:58,250
Why bother standing
on the battlefield?

39
00:04:00,166 --> 00:04:01,250
Weakling.

40
00:04:06,583 --> 00:04:08,833
All this violence.
For what?

41
00:04:08,916 --> 00:04:10,208
It’s unreal.

42
00:04:10,291 --> 00:04:13,083
Only a small detachment
did this much damage?

43
00:04:13,166 --> 00:04:15,125
Nothing about this
is surprising.

44
00:04:15,208 --> 00:04:18,250
We’re dealing with a Fairy
Soldier, a genuine warrior.

45
00:04:18,333 --> 00:04:19,541
You’re genuine, sir.

46
00:04:19,625 --> 00:04:21,958
You also fought
in the War of Unification.

47
00:04:24,625 --> 00:04:26,083
That’s right, I served.

48
00:04:26,166 --> 00:04:29,333
With the director gone,
I’ll have to stop Liscar.

49
00:04:29,416 --> 00:04:30,833
-[objects clatter]
-[FREE gasps]

50
00:04:33,125 --> 00:04:34,958
Ah! Dorothea! Perfect.

51
00:04:35,041 --> 00:04:36,833
Allies. It’s about time!

52
00:04:36,916 --> 00:04:38,333
Military Minister Bohme?

53
00:04:38,416 --> 00:04:41,291
Quickly! You can team-up
with us under my command.

54
00:04:41,375 --> 00:04:43,833
We can outmaneuver them
but we must go now, hurry!

55
00:04:43,916 --> 00:04:45,208
It’s your call.

56
00:04:45,291 --> 00:04:46,500
Are you sure
we want to listen

57
00:04:46,583 --> 00:04:47,791
to this guy’s strategy?

58
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:51,708
All right.

59
00:04:56,125 --> 00:04:59,625
Several years ago,
back in 481 U.E.

60
00:04:59,708 --> 00:05:01,708
Golbarn was the king of Cidal.

61
00:05:01,791 --> 00:05:04,833
The emperor gave
an imperial command

62
00:05:04,916 --> 00:05:07,041
for the king
to assemble his forces

63
00:05:07,125 --> 00:05:10,958
and launch an invasion
into neighboring Timoon.

64
00:05:11,041 --> 00:05:14,416
At that time,
nobody could’ve predicted

65
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:16,625
Cidal would
achieve unification.

66
00:05:16,708 --> 00:05:18,291
It was unimaginable.

67
00:05:19,541 --> 00:05:21,833
I was only a child
at the time.

68
00:05:21,916 --> 00:05:25,166
True. Twenty-four years
is quite a while.

69
00:05:25,250 --> 00:05:28,291
I was already serving
in the Ainedern military.

70
00:05:28,375 --> 00:05:30,000
Attacking Timoon,

71
00:05:30,083 --> 00:05:32,541
it seemed more insane
than reckless.

72
00:05:32,625 --> 00:05:34,083
You could hardly
blame me for thinking

73
00:05:34,166 --> 00:05:35,833
the order was falsified.

74
00:05:35,916 --> 00:05:37,500
However...

75
00:05:37,583 --> 00:05:39,583
[WOLF] According to history,
Garlan Battle,

76
00:05:39,666 --> 00:05:41,375
the famed
Knight of Cidal,

77
00:05:41,458 --> 00:05:43,208
was tasked
with removing the emperor

78
00:05:43,291 --> 00:05:45,375
from the imperial capital
of Mazria.

79
00:05:45,458 --> 00:05:49,500
At the time, it was under
the Kingdom of Ledrad’s control.

80
00:05:49,583 --> 00:05:51,750
Everything changed
after that incident.

81
00:05:51,833 --> 00:05:53,250
[DIESE]
Indeed.

82
00:05:53,333 --> 00:05:56,125
The power structure
was built around two aspects:

83
00:05:56,208 --> 00:05:58,583
Ledrad’s manipulation
of the emperor,

84
00:05:58,666 --> 00:06:01,625
and my native Ainedern
acting as their accomplice.

85
00:06:01,708 --> 00:06:04,333
Power structure.
Meaning what?

86
00:06:04,416 --> 00:06:06,541
Conflict used to be
never-ending.

87
00:06:06,625 --> 00:06:08,916
Though one truth
remained constant.

88
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:12,416
Ledrad and Ainedern’s supremacy
was never in question.

89
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:13,833
[WOLF]
I see.

90
00:06:13,916 --> 00:06:16,416
But Golbarn was able
to overturn that framework

91
00:06:16,500 --> 00:06:18,708
by obtaining a crucial
playing piece:

92
00:06:18,791 --> 00:06:19,916
the emperor.

93
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:22,708
Golbarn’s a shrewd,
calculating man.

94
00:06:22,791 --> 00:06:24,875
I was convinced that
after Unification

95
00:06:24,958 --> 00:06:28,000
he’d find some way to install
himself as the new emperor.

96
00:06:28,083 --> 00:06:30,833
[WOLF] And yet, he remained
a loyal subject.

97
00:06:30,916 --> 00:06:32,000
[DIESE scoffs]

98
00:06:32,083 --> 00:06:33,458
You’re a fool
if you think that.

99
00:06:33,541 --> 00:06:34,875
It was fear.

100
00:06:34,958 --> 00:06:37,666
The fear of forever
being branded a usurper.

101
00:06:37,750 --> 00:06:38,666
[heavy thud]

102
00:06:38,750 --> 00:06:40,750
Eizenkopf! Crush these pebbles!

103
00:06:40,833 --> 00:06:43,666
[EIZENKOPF grunting]

104
00:06:43,750 --> 00:06:46,458
Men! Stand your ground for
His Imperial Majesty--

105
00:06:49,916 --> 00:06:51,083
Smells like death.

106
00:06:51,166 --> 00:06:52,375
[EIZENKOPF snarling]

107
00:06:52,458 --> 00:06:55,166
Peace rots a soldier
from the inside out,

108
00:06:55,250 --> 00:06:56,875
and this place stinks of it.

109
00:06:56,958 --> 00:06:59,458
[roaring continues]

110
00:07:00,583 --> 00:07:01,708
[MAN grunts]

111
00:07:03,625 --> 00:07:05,208
[grunts] Reinforcements!

112
00:07:08,250 --> 00:07:09,458
We’re falling back for now!

113
00:07:11,208 --> 00:07:12,291
-[MAN grunts]
-[stone shifting]

114
00:07:19,708 --> 00:07:22,166
I never knew
these passages existed.

115
00:07:22,250 --> 00:07:25,166
You’ll find the royal palace
is home to many secrets.

116
00:07:25,250 --> 00:07:27,958
And there’s no single person
that’s aware of all of them.

117
00:07:31,583 --> 00:07:32,833
[EIZENKOPF roaring]

118
00:07:32,916 --> 00:07:34,583
They’re right below us.

119
00:07:34,666 --> 00:07:36,791
[BOHME]
Exactly as I predicted.

120
00:07:36,875 --> 00:07:39,000
This way we can get
the drop on them.

121
00:07:39,083 --> 00:07:40,125
[chuckling]

122
00:07:40,208 --> 00:07:41,583
Minister Bohme!

123
00:07:41,666 --> 00:07:44,791
-News, soldier?
-Sir! Word from the West Gate!

124
00:07:44,875 --> 00:07:47,333
Reinforcements have arrived
and are joining the fight!

125
00:07:47,416 --> 00:07:50,375
Excellent! And who’s
their commanding officer?

126
00:07:50,458 --> 00:07:51,791
[MESSENGER]
Actually...

127
00:07:51,875 --> 00:07:54,416
[SOLDIERS yelling]

128
00:07:58,208 --> 00:08:00,416
Did you think I’d stand by
and do nothing?

129
00:08:00,500 --> 00:08:03,708
It’s my responsibility
to defend Rondacia,

130
00:08:03,791 --> 00:08:05,875
and I’ll be damned
if I let some pack of rebels

131
00:08:05,958 --> 00:08:07,791
turn it into their war zone.

132
00:08:07,875 --> 00:08:09,333
[SOLDIER A]
Don't stop firing!

133
00:08:09,416 --> 00:08:11,041
[SOLDIER B] Keep putting
the pressure on them!

134
00:08:11,125 --> 00:08:12,916
Guess no one
told these idiots

135
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:15,125
their ammunition
will eventually run out.

136
00:08:16,375 --> 00:08:18,000
[BEEVEE]
Just like old days.

137
00:08:18,083 --> 00:08:20,708
Used to be like this
all the time

138
00:08:20,791 --> 00:08:22,541
during the War of Unification...

139
00:08:22,625 --> 00:08:25,125
before everyone went soft.

140
00:08:25,208 --> 00:08:27,666
Feeling nostalgic, sir?

141
00:08:27,750 --> 00:08:29,916
I live and breathe for this.

142
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:31,291
[DIPPER scoffs]

143
00:08:32,583 --> 00:08:33,708
[gunfire ceases]

144
00:08:34,916 --> 00:08:36,500
[BEEVEE]
That’s my cue.

145
00:08:39,791 --> 00:08:40,833
[SOLDIERS groaning]

146
00:08:43,125 --> 00:08:44,833
[laughs sinisterly]

147
00:08:45,916 --> 00:08:47,750
[EIZENKOPF roaring]

148
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:51,500
Hold fast! We’re not
moving from this spot

149
00:08:51,583 --> 00:08:52,708
until he’s dead on the floor!

150
00:08:55,916 --> 00:08:57,041
[BEEVEE]
Here’s your chance.

151
00:08:57,125 --> 00:08:58,500
Fight me.

152
00:08:58,583 --> 00:09:01,708
I’m right here.
Don’t hold back.

153
00:09:01,791 --> 00:09:04,958
♪

154
00:09:07,666 --> 00:09:09,041
[EIZENKOPF grunts]

155
00:09:09,125 --> 00:09:10,708
I’m waiting!

156
00:09:10,791 --> 00:09:12,583
Prove to me
you’re more than just dirt!

157
00:09:12,666 --> 00:09:14,625
Take this mad man down!

158
00:09:14,708 --> 00:09:16,708
You can either run
or stand your ground.

159
00:09:19,375 --> 00:09:21,625
Where you die
is entirely up to you.

160
00:09:22,833 --> 00:09:24,625
Follow behind the colonel!

161
00:09:38,625 --> 00:09:40,625
[MARLYA]
I don’t understand it.

162
00:09:40,708 --> 00:09:43,000
Why do people fight?

163
00:09:43,083 --> 00:09:46,000
What could be worth
all this bloodshed?

164
00:09:46,083 --> 00:09:48,083
I can’t think
of a single thing.

165
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,625
War brings death.

166
00:09:52,708 --> 00:09:54,500
But no one wants to die.

167
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,583
[MARLYA panting]

168
00:10:03,958 --> 00:10:06,750
[footsteps approaching]

169
00:10:06,833 --> 00:10:09,000
Looks like Free and the others
haven’t started,

170
00:10:09,083 --> 00:10:10,791
so just hang tight.

171
00:10:12,833 --> 00:10:13,875
[MARLYA chuckles softly]

172
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:16,958
This is where we part ways.

173
00:10:17,041 --> 00:10:18,583
I’ll be seeing you soon.

174
00:10:29,458 --> 00:10:30,708
[OZZ screams]

175
00:10:33,791 --> 00:10:34,791
[MARLYA]
No.

176
00:10:34,875 --> 00:10:36,958
I’m not
running away anymore.

177
00:10:37,041 --> 00:10:39,750
This Liscar guy has to pay
for what he did!

178
00:10:55,250 --> 00:10:56,208
Time to go.

179
00:10:56,291 --> 00:10:57,791
-Minister!
-[BOHME] Hmm?

180
00:10:57,875 --> 00:11:00,166
I was about to.
Forward, men!

181
00:11:00,250 --> 00:11:01,875
[SOLDIERS shouting]

182
00:11:03,750 --> 00:11:05,458
[shouting continues in distance]

183
00:11:05,541 --> 00:11:06,750
Oh.

184
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:08,625
Sounds like
we’re gonna have company.

185
00:11:08,708 --> 00:11:09,958
Open fire!

186
00:11:11,291 --> 00:11:13,208
[gunfire continues in distance]

187
00:11:13,291 --> 00:11:14,666
[FREE]
Ozz.

188
00:11:14,750 --> 00:11:17,333
I’m not going to ask you
to help me out here.

189
00:11:17,416 --> 00:11:20,041
Just watch,
wherever you are!

190
00:11:24,375 --> 00:11:26,250
I’ve been waiting for this.

191
00:11:39,583 --> 00:11:42,041
-[metal scraping]
-[MEN grunting]

192
00:11:48,250 --> 00:11:51,333
-Better than last time.
-You don’t say?

193
00:11:51,416 --> 00:11:52,625
[BEEVEE laughs mockingly]

194
00:11:52,708 --> 00:11:54,708
[FREE grunting]

195
00:11:55,958 --> 00:11:57,708
[blades humming]

196
00:11:57,791 --> 00:11:58,958
[BEEVEE chuckles]

197
00:12:00,375 --> 00:12:02,166
Well done!
That’s more like it!

198
00:12:02,250 --> 00:12:03,583
I don’t need your praise.

199
00:12:03,666 --> 00:12:05,125
I’ll cut you down to size.

200
00:12:08,541 --> 00:12:10,375
He’s on par with the colonel.

201
00:12:10,458 --> 00:12:11,416
[gunshot]

202
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:13,333
If we don’t stop them,

203
00:12:13,416 --> 00:12:15,458
the fighting will never end!

204
00:12:18,541 --> 00:12:19,958
Sir, look out! From the rear!

205
00:12:20,041 --> 00:12:22,625
-Wake up and face reality!
-[metal scraping]

206
00:12:22,708 --> 00:12:24,875
This isn’t the age
of war anymore!

207
00:12:24,958 --> 00:12:27,083
Nobody wants this but you!

208
00:12:27,166 --> 00:12:28,541
[BEEVEE scoffs]

209
00:12:28,625 --> 00:12:30,333
[BEEVEE]
Doesn’t matter what age it is.

210
00:12:34,375 --> 00:12:35,750
[power hums]

211
00:12:37,375 --> 00:12:39,791
Times change, but I don’t!

212
00:12:39,875 --> 00:12:41,916
[roars]

213
00:12:46,750 --> 00:12:48,583
Look, Free. See that?

214
00:12:48,666 --> 00:12:51,458
When you’re overcome with fear
and lose sight of the goal,

215
00:12:51,541 --> 00:12:53,000
that’s your destination.

216
00:12:53,083 --> 00:12:54,916
Move forward.

217
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:57,000
[FREE] I will, Jet.
Thank you.

218
00:12:57,083 --> 00:12:59,916
-[EIZENKOPF roars]
-[metallic scraping]

219
00:13:02,291 --> 00:13:03,125
[FREE grunts]

220
00:13:04,541 --> 00:13:06,750
-[energy humming]
-[FREE grunting]

221
00:13:06,833 --> 00:13:08,708
♪

222
00:13:17,791 --> 00:13:19,458
[BEEVEE scoffs]

223
00:13:19,541 --> 00:13:22,083
[SOPHIE] Follow the colonel.
He’s heading outside!

224
00:13:22,166 --> 00:13:23,000
[inhales sharply]

225
00:13:29,416 --> 00:13:30,541
[snarls]

226
00:13:35,166 --> 00:13:36,500
[RED HOOD snarls]

227
00:13:36,583 --> 00:13:38,958
[roaring]

228
00:13:40,375 --> 00:13:41,708
[groans]

229
00:13:43,041 --> 00:13:44,625
Yes! More!
Keep going!

230
00:13:44,708 --> 00:13:46,750
This is what
I’ve been waiting for!

231
00:13:46,833 --> 00:13:48,125
You almost remind me
of the man

232
00:13:48,208 --> 00:13:49,541
who originally held that sword,

233
00:13:49,625 --> 00:13:51,500
like I was dueling
Jet Grave again!

234
00:13:51,583 --> 00:13:53,375
You talk too much!

235
00:14:00,041 --> 00:14:01,958
[EIZENKOPF roars]

236
00:14:12,708 --> 00:14:16,166
You’re close,
but not there.

237
00:14:16,250 --> 00:14:18,500
What? You think I don’t
already know that?

238
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:21,958
[EIZENKOPF snarls]

239
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:24,166
[EIZENKOPF roaring]

240
00:14:25,458 --> 00:14:26,666
I’m not alone.

241
00:14:26,750 --> 00:14:29,041
My goal was never
to beat you one-on-one.

242
00:14:31,750 --> 00:14:33,208
[MARLYA]
Can you hear me, Ozz?

243
00:14:33,291 --> 00:14:35,208
Your comrades will avenge you!

244
00:14:37,500 --> 00:14:39,708
[groans]
Told you we’d meet again!

245
00:14:41,500 --> 00:14:42,458
Look out!

246
00:14:46,458 --> 00:14:50,458
We fight as one,
because we’re Dorothea!

247
00:14:52,416 --> 00:14:54,750
[footsteps echoing]

248
00:14:57,666 --> 00:14:59,750
[DIESE]
It won’t be much longer.

249
00:14:59,833 --> 00:15:03,125
[WOLF] I’m surprised Christopher
Rahn pledged allegiance.

250
00:15:03,208 --> 00:15:05,666
The man’s a surviving
Ledrad royal after all.

251
00:15:05,750 --> 00:15:07,000
[DIESE scoffs]
Thanks to him,

252
00:15:07,083 --> 00:15:09,666
I procured
the blueprints to the palace.

253
00:15:09,750 --> 00:15:12,750
Make no mistake.
He’s not my only collaborator.

254
00:15:12,833 --> 00:15:15,291
[WOLF] There are many
who support you,

255
00:15:15,375 --> 00:15:17,666
and the reform
you’ll bring to the world.

256
00:15:17,750 --> 00:15:20,166
Correct.
Once this is done,

257
00:15:20,250 --> 00:15:22,416
and we’ve removed the emperor,

258
00:15:22,500 --> 00:15:25,041
the opposing forces
feigning loyalty to Golbarn

259
00:15:25,125 --> 00:15:26,916
will begin defecting en masse.

260
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:28,541
After they pledge fealty,

261
00:15:28,625 --> 00:15:32,083
Unified Zesskia
will lose its support.

262
00:15:32,166 --> 00:15:34,166
[WOLF]
You’ve worked it all out.

263
00:15:36,291 --> 00:15:37,708
-[keys jingling]
-[door unlocking]

264
00:15:37,791 --> 00:15:39,750
♪

265
00:15:48,750 --> 00:15:49,583
[FREE grunts]

266
00:15:51,708 --> 00:15:53,208
Don’t stop now.

267
00:15:53,291 --> 00:15:55,208
I haven’t had a fight
this good in ages!

268
00:15:55,291 --> 00:15:57,750
Stop treating it
like some kind of game!

269
00:15:57,833 --> 00:16:01,708
[EIZENKOPF roars]

270
00:16:01,791 --> 00:16:03,208
[FREE grunting]

271
00:16:04,250 --> 00:16:05,083
[BOTH grunt]

272
00:16:05,166 --> 00:16:06,375
[BEEVEE chuckles]

273
00:16:06,458 --> 00:16:07,583
[BEEVEE grunts]

274
00:16:07,666 --> 00:16:09,333
[inhales sharply]
This guy.

275
00:16:12,250 --> 00:16:14,083
Looks like
we reached our limit.

276
00:16:14,166 --> 00:16:15,958
Colonel! Come on!
Don't tell me

277
00:16:16,041 --> 00:16:18,291
this will be our last time
fighting together. [grunts]

278
00:16:18,375 --> 00:16:20,666
We’re finished here!
Make the call!

279
00:16:20,750 --> 00:16:23,083
♪

280
00:16:24,458 --> 00:16:25,291
[BEEVEE groans]

281
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:29,833
Enough for tonight!

282
00:16:29,916 --> 00:16:31,291
[BOTH chuckle]

283
00:16:40,541 --> 00:16:41,625
[KLARA gasps]

284
00:16:41,708 --> 00:16:42,708
What is it?

285
00:16:42,791 --> 00:16:44,041
Tell me, do you see something?

286
00:16:47,250 --> 00:16:49,875
It’s the enemy.
They’re withdrawing!

287
00:16:52,291 --> 00:16:53,458
[MARLYA hisses]

288
00:16:53,541 --> 00:16:55,458
-[wind whistles]
-[coughing]

289
00:16:55,541 --> 00:16:56,958
You won’t get away!

290
00:16:57,041 --> 00:16:59,125
♪

291
00:17:02,541 --> 00:17:03,375
[DIESE]
Hmm.

292
00:17:17,875 --> 00:17:19,708
[GARRISON LEADER]
Who goes there?

293
00:17:19,791 --> 00:17:22,125
I’ve come to demand an audience

294
00:17:22,208 --> 00:17:24,125
with his Imperial Majesty.

295
00:17:24,208 --> 00:17:27,708
You will grant me entrance
to the throne room immediately!

296
00:17:27,791 --> 00:17:30,041
[GARRISON LEADER] It’s him!
Duke Hybranz!

297
00:17:30,125 --> 00:17:32,583
You’re mistaken.
I am no longer a Duke.

298
00:17:32,666 --> 00:17:36,416
My one true title is and
always will be Schwarz Diese!

299
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:39,083
You’re a traitor!
Guards!

300
00:17:39,166 --> 00:17:40,541
[GARRISON LEADER groans]

301
00:17:42,958 --> 00:17:44,250
[SOLDIERS gasping]

302
00:17:44,333 --> 00:17:48,041
It’s imperative I see
His Majesty at once!

303
00:17:48,125 --> 00:17:49,833
Don’t make me repeat myself!

304
00:17:54,458 --> 00:17:56,083
[MARLYA panting]

305
00:17:56,166 --> 00:17:57,583
Outta the way!

306
00:17:59,333 --> 00:18:01,333
Marlya!
Where are you running to?

307
00:18:04,041 --> 00:18:06,583
-[gunfire]
-[heavy thudding]

308
00:18:13,041 --> 00:18:14,708
[CASTAL]
Tell me.

309
00:18:14,791 --> 00:18:17,500
Why are you
disturbing my peace?

310
00:18:18,666 --> 00:18:20,708
Why?
For your sake.

311
00:18:20,791 --> 00:18:22,333
Isn’t that clear?

312
00:18:23,708 --> 00:18:25,208
Hmm?

313
00:18:25,291 --> 00:18:27,666
Where’s Wolfran run off to?

314
00:18:27,750 --> 00:18:31,000
I could’ve sworn he was
following right behind us.

315
00:18:31,083 --> 00:18:33,833
[RAY]
He performed his duty admirably

316
00:18:33,916 --> 00:18:35,333
and had to depart.

317
00:18:35,416 --> 00:18:36,666
[DIESE]
Hmm?

318
00:18:36,750 --> 00:18:38,916
♪

319
00:18:44,708 --> 00:18:46,625
Didn’t expect to see you.

320
00:18:50,333 --> 00:18:52,625
Ray Dawn.

321
00:18:52,708 --> 00:18:54,208
How’d you--?

322
00:18:54,291 --> 00:18:56,041
Never mind. It’s obvious.

323
00:18:56,125 --> 00:18:58,875
Wolfran’s been working
for you all along!

324
00:18:58,958 --> 00:19:00,458
[RAY]
You know too much.

325
00:19:00,541 --> 00:19:02,666
No good can come from that.

326
00:19:02,750 --> 00:19:04,708
♪

327
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:12,375
[SOLDIERS gasping]

328
00:19:12,458 --> 00:19:15,250
-It’s rust.
-It’s called Throne Taker.

329
00:19:15,333 --> 00:19:17,250
That’s his fairy’s ability.

330
00:19:17,333 --> 00:19:19,208
-[DIESE grunts]
-Hmm?

331
00:19:19,291 --> 00:19:20,708
Unfortunately,

332
00:19:20,791 --> 00:19:23,000
you have no understanding
of the times.

333
00:19:25,791 --> 00:19:27,041
[SOLDIERS screaming]

334
00:19:27,125 --> 00:19:28,500
What’s happening?

335
00:19:31,458 --> 00:19:32,916
[loud boom]

336
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:34,583
[EIZENKOPF snarling]

337
00:19:37,291 --> 00:19:39,166
[EIZENKOPF roars]

338
00:19:40,708 --> 00:19:43,625
It can’t be.
Beevee Liscar is here?

339
00:19:43,708 --> 00:19:45,458
All of you!
Protect the prime minister!

340
00:19:49,458 --> 00:19:50,750
-[COMMANDER groans]
-[GOLBARN gasps]

341
00:19:53,166 --> 00:19:54,625
[EIZENKOPF roars]

342
00:19:54,708 --> 00:19:57,125
We can’t defeat them.
Retreat!

343
00:19:57,208 --> 00:19:58,875
We’ll find another way inside!

344
00:19:58,958 --> 00:20:01,875
[shuddering]

345
00:20:11,833 --> 00:20:13,500
Why, Ray Dawn?

346
00:20:13,583 --> 00:20:17,000
If you possessed such
tremendous power all along,

347
00:20:17,083 --> 00:20:20,166
why stand by
as Golbarn’s sycophant?

348
00:20:21,666 --> 00:20:24,000
Perhaps I should’ve
told you this sooner,

349
00:20:24,083 --> 00:20:25,916
but I despise you.

350
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:28,625
Your shallowness
and cavalier attitude.

351
00:20:28,708 --> 00:20:31,250
-Irritating qualities.
-[DIESE moaning]

352
00:20:32,333 --> 00:20:35,458
You’ll be forever known
as Schwarz Diese, the traitor.

353
00:20:35,541 --> 00:20:37,875
Not even death
will bring atonement.

354
00:20:37,958 --> 00:20:40,833
History will never forgive those
who betray His Majesty,

355
00:20:40,916 --> 00:20:42,291
the emperor.

356
00:20:43,458 --> 00:20:44,833
[moans]

357
00:20:44,916 --> 00:20:47,458
♪

358
00:20:57,291 --> 00:20:59,500
Look at the carnage
they left behind.

359
00:20:59,583 --> 00:21:01,958
Those guys really were trying
to start another war.

360
00:21:02,041 --> 00:21:04,208
-[grunts] And they still can!
-[KLARA gasps]

361
00:21:04,291 --> 00:21:06,583
-[FREE] Wait, Marlya!
-Let me go!

362
00:21:06,666 --> 00:21:08,875
-He’s so close!
-And then what?

363
00:21:09,875 --> 00:21:12,000
Is the only thing
you want revenge?

364
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:17,250
We drove the enemy forces
out of the palace.

365
00:21:17,333 --> 00:21:20,291
The battle’s done.
We performed our duty.

366
00:21:20,375 --> 00:21:21,375
[MARLYA inhales sharply]

367
00:21:21,458 --> 00:21:23,416
And what about justice for...?

368
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:24,458
[crying]

369
00:21:24,541 --> 00:21:26,875
Is victory enough for you?

370
00:21:30,750 --> 00:21:31,750
It is.

371
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:34,541
[MARLYA breathes shakily]

372
00:21:34,625 --> 00:21:38,750
So we really won today,
didn’t we?

373
00:21:38,833 --> 00:21:40,000
We did.

374
00:21:40,083 --> 00:21:42,541
They attacked, we fought back...

375
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:45,708
and won.

376
00:21:45,791 --> 00:21:48,541
♪

377
00:23:38,541 --> 00:23:41,250
[FREE] And just like that,
the war was over.

378
00:23:41,333 --> 00:23:42,583
[WOLF]
What’s your reason for fighting?

379
00:23:42,666 --> 00:23:44,208
What are you protecting?

380
00:23:44,291 --> 00:23:45,708
[VERONICA] You can’t get back
what’s already lost!

381
00:23:45,791 --> 00:23:47,041
[MARLYA]
Even if you get your revenge,

382
00:23:47,125 --> 00:23:48,416
it won’t change the past!

